profile_positions.description:
Responsible for business development, sales & account management in an international environment, with a focus on the EMEA & APAC regions. Frequent business travel, up to 40% international. Managing small tender teams and having a leading role towards inside sales & account managers. Reporting directly to CEO. 

•	First point of contact to enterprise clients in Oil & Gas, Offshore, Chemicals, Infrastructure and EPC throughout sales process from initiation to contracting and account management; 
•	Leading tenders for software implementations (licenses & services) from RFI to contract negotiations. Hosting extensive demo presentations, writing proposals and leading up to tender teams;
•	Contributing to the commercial strategy of the company, actively proposing and implementing improvements in our sales & marketing approach;
•	Initiating business development in the APAC region, researching the possibilities to establish a new sales office in Australia. Building pipeline, closing deals and established a partner network to support our local activities; 
•	Involved in defining the approach and planning software implementations, monitoring progress and acting as a second line for client escalation;
•	Contributing to marketing activities such as business fairs, i.e. as expert speaker on international events. 

Accomplishments: 
•	Sales of major software implementations (including 7-figure deals) to various industry leading companies including Global Fortune 500 companies;
•	Development of multiple smaller clients to key accounts through a combined services approach;
•	Implemented various improvements in the company's commercial approach, i.e. in lead qualification, proposal to closure, account management.

•	Development of customer relations with major commercial potential in the South-West region of the Netherlands. Functionally leading up to Junior Commercial Consultants, facilitating them in their recruitment activities for entry and professional level positions;
•	Independent recruitment and mediation of senior professionals in technical, commercial and management positions with leading technical companies in the maritime & offshore industry; 
•	Member of the corporate steering team

•	Operational and functional management of a commercial team with up to 3 FTE, including training of two new Junior Commercial Consultants. Initiating both personal coaching as well as group training; 
•	Operationally responsible for the commercial result of the office; 
•	Steering the commercial focus of the Commercial Consultants and guidance (especially in final phase) of the commercial completion of sales contracts;
•	Recruitment and account management for key accounts. 

Accomplishment: 
•	Trebled the number of successful mediations of the team in the first quarter of my promotion, compared to the previous quarter.
